# SHARED / TYPES — cross-cutting / global TypeScript types & ambient declarations
# not owned by any single feature (utility types, asset/module declarations,
# environment typing).
#
# Feature-local types stay in features/<feature>/types (FOLDER_STRUCTURE.md §3.1).
# Content SCHEMAS live in the content layer (CONTENT_MODEL.md), not here.
# Follow CODING_STANDARDS §1: `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions.
